The paper discusses a framework for analyzing the citation impact of scientific publications, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The focus on citation impact suggests that the paper may be relevant to sub-categories such as digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The analysis of highly cited publications may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cryptography (cs.CR) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
